   <concept id="FAR_49_304_1" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">49.304-1</ph> General.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d2901e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2928e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            In a partial termination, the TCO shall limit the settlement to an adjustment of the fee, if any, and with the concurrence of the contracting office to a reduction in the estimated cost. The TCO shall adjust the fee as provided in <xref href="49.304-2.dita#FAR_49_304_2"
                        base="i1068269"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">49.304-2</xref> and <xref href="49.305.dita#FAR_49_305"
                        base="i1068286"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">49.305</xref>, unless-</p>
               <ol id="d2901e29" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2928e22">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                The terminated portion is clearly severable from the balance of the contract; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d2928e27">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                Performance of the contract is virtually complete, or performance of any continued portion is only on subsidiary items or spare parts, or is otherwise not substantial.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d2928e32">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            In the case of the exceptions in paragraph (a), the procedures in <xref href="49.302.dita#FAR_49_302"
                        base="i1068192"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">49.302</xref> and <xref href="49.303.dita#FAR_49_303"
                        base="i1068211"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">49.303</xref> apply.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
</dita>
